body: Hi! You do not need to extract any model, just use it as is.
I am also running into similar issue. I downloaded the pre-trained model from Google Drive and ran Step 3 of Training but it returns a sequence of WARNING saying no pre-trained parameters found.
Do you meant to train a model on pre-trained MobileNet v1 weights or do inference on a pre-trained model?

It is ok. We use pre-trained on ImageNet weights of MobileNet v1 classification network to initialize pose estimation model, so weights related to pose estimation part of the network are missed in it (and that is because it warnings, not errors), see #70.

issue.title: can‘t perform step3

repository.name: lightweight-human-pose-estimation.pytorch
repository.description: Fast and accurate human pose estimation in PyTorch. Contains implementation of "Real-time 2D Multi-Person Pose Estimation on CPU: Lightweight OpenPose" paper.
